http://www.thehindu.com/news/international/U.S-will-be-partner-in-Vibrant-Gujarat-2017/article14460643.ece

 The U.S will be a “partner country” in the 2017 Vibrant Gujarat investors’ summit, Assistant Secretary of State for South and Central Asian Affairs Nisha Biswal has said.Ms. Biswal made the announcement at a meeting with a Gujarat State delegation, led by Resident Commissioner Bharat Lal, and accompanied by Indian Charge d’Affaires Ambassador Taranjit Singh Sandhu, a State Department statement said. “The Assistant Secretary praised Resident Commissioner Lal for his efforts to make the State of Gujarat a model of innovation and sustainable economic growth and reform for India. She also announced the United States’ intent to participate as a Partner Country in the 2017 Vibrant Gujarat Global Summit, the government of Gujarat’s biennial investors’ summit that brings together global business leaders, investors, corporations, thought leaders, and policymakers,” the statement said.In 2015, U.S. Secretary of State John Kerry had led the U.S delegation to the Vibrant Gujarat Summit. 